@startuml
title BP-20 - Due Date and Overdue Processing

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  DiamondBackgroundColor White
  DiamondBorderColor Black
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
}

|Billing Engine|
start
:Run scheduled due date check;
:Find obligations with outstanding amount greater than zero;
:Compare due date with current date;

if (Obligation overdue?) then (Yes)
  :Mark as overdue for reporting;
  if (Penalty rule configured?) then (Yes)
    :Apply penalty after grace period;
  else (No)
    :Keep amount unchanged;
  endif
  :Prepare reminder notification;
else (No)
  :Keep obligation as normal outstanding;
endif

|Notification Engine|
:Send due date or overdue reminder;

|Finance Officer|
:View overdue report;
stop

note right
Current MVP has due date filters and outstanding bills.
Overdue status, penalty and scheduled notifications are future scope.
end note
@enduml
